OL,10,Fthe jury carefully considered the
OL,11,Fevidence and came to what is
OL,12,Fabsolutely the correct conclusion.
OL,14,F"Cox's patients had every right to
OL,15,Ffeel safe and to trust him, but he
OL,16,Fcompletely betrayed this trust,
OL,17,Fembarking on a series of indecent
OL,18,Fassaults which his victims have had to
